14/09/2004
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- The first Greek-language school has opened in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC), according to separate statements by the UN and the TRNC government Monday (13 September). The secondary school was set up in the Greek Cypriot enclave of Rizokarpasso with the help of the UN peacekeeping force. The Greek Cypriot administration in the south of the island was asked to help find teachers for the new school. (UN Web site, NTV - 13/09/04)
